-- European Stocks Retreat; Stoxx 600 Declines 0.5 Percent
-- B y   S a r a h   J o n e s
-- 2013-06-19T07:35:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-19/european-stocks-retreat-stoxx-600-declines-0-5-percent.html
European stocks declined as
investors awaited the conclusion of the  Federal Reserve ’s
policy meeting for indications on stimulus measures. U.S. index
futures were little changed, while Asian shares rose.  Alcatel-Lucent SA rallied 5.2 percent after announcing
plans to sell at least 1 billion euros ($1.3 billion) of assets.
Nordea Bank AB dropped 3.7 percent after  Sweden  began selling a
stake in the Nordic region’s largest bank.  The Stoxx Europe 600 Index declined 0.4 percent to 291.83
as of 8:33 a.m. in London, erasing earlier gains. Standard &
Poor’s 500 Index futures fell 0.1 percent after the U.S. gauge
advanced 1.5 percent over the past two days. The MSCI Asia
Pacific Index climbed 1 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
